    <text>
        <body>
             <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">              
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><name>ᚊ<supplied reason="lost">ᚓ</supplied>ᚉᚉ<supplied reason="lost">ᚔᚐᚄ</supplied></name> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">ᚋ<supplied reason="lost">ᚒ</supplied>ᚉ<supplied reason="lost">ᚑᚔ</w> <name>ᚁ</supplied>ᚏ<supplied reason="lost">ᚑ</supplied>ᚓ<supplied reason="lost">ᚅᚔᚑᚅᚐᚄ</supplied></name></persName>
                </ab> 
            </div>                    
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" xml:space="preserve" resp="#POC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><name>Q<supplied reason="lost">E</supplied>CC<supplied reason="lost">IAS</supplied></name> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">M<supplied reason="lost">U</supplied>C<supplied reason="lost">OI</w> <name>B</supplied>R<supplied reason="lost">O</supplied>E<supplied reason="lost">NIONAS</supplied></name></persName>
                </ab>
                <ab type="list">Q[E]CC[IAS] M[U]C[OI B]R[O]E[NIONAS]</ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app n="1">
                        <note>Macalister (1945, 287) supplied a restoration, filling the gaps in the inscription. The possible presence of the formula word MUCOI suggests that the inscription likely followed the X descendent of Y formula.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>'of Bróen?'</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The name BROINIONAS is recorded in three other ogham inscriptions ((I-COR-071) Monataggart, Co. Cork; (I-KER-018) Ballinrannig, Co. Kerry and (I-WAT-019) Drumlohan, Co Waterford). However, the reading is only relatively certain in (I-KER-018) Ballinrannig, Co. Kerry, which has the expected ending -IONAS and in (I-COR-071) Monataggart, Co. Cork, which has BROINIENAS.</p>
            </div>
